Package org.lgdcloudsim.user

Class UserRequestManagerGoogleTrace

java.lang.Object
org.lgdcloudsim.user.UserRequestManagerGoogleTrace
All Implemented Interfaces:
UserRequestManager
public class UserRequestManagerGoogleTrace extends Object implements UserRequestManager
UserRequestManagerGoogleTrace is an implementation of the UserRequestManager interface. It is responsible for generating user requests from thethe Google cluster trace We have organized the 10,000 user request data in each cluster data into csv files. The contents contained in the csv file are: time,user,collection_id,instance_index,cpus,ram,collection_type Those with the same user form a user request, and those with the same collection_id form an instance group in the user request, and each instance_index represents an instance. Since the values of CPU and Ram have been normalized, you need to set the maximum value yourself to make the CPU and Ram a reasonable size. The storage and bandwidth values are not provided by the Google cluster trace, so we need to randomly generate them ourselves. It is recommended to generate some smaller values so as not to affect scheduling. The life cycle of the instance also needs to be set by yourself.
Since:
LGDCloudSim 1.0
Author:
Anonymous
